# {{ProjectName}} (Layered Solution)

This solution uses four projects:

- Domain — Entities + domain events (no external deps)
- Application — Use-case services, repository abstractions, IEventBus abstraction
- Infrastructure — EF Core DbContext + repository implementations
- Web — ASP.NET Core MVC app with HTMX + Swap.Htmx wiring, event chains, adapters, views

Dev stack and tooling mirrors `swap-monolith`:

- HTMX via LibMan (see `Web/libman.json`)
- Tailwind + DaisyUI via NPM (see `Web/package.json`)
- Docker + Compose for containerized runs (see `Web/Dockerfile`, `Web/docker-compose.yml`)

See `Web/README.md` for run instructions.
# {{ProjectName}} (Layered, Multi-Project)

Solution structure:

- Domain — Entities and domain events (no external deps)
- Application — Use-case services and abstractions (IEventBus, repositories)
- Infrastructure — EF Core DbContext and repository implementations
- Web — ASP.NET Core MVC app, HTMX + Swap.Htmx wiring, event chains, adapters, views

Key points:

- Controllers depend on Application services, not DbContext
- Application emits domain events via IEventBus; Web adapts to Swap.Htmx
- UI refresh uses HTMX-native `ui.*` events (see `Web/Events/SwapEventChains.cs`)

Getting started:

1. Configure `Web/appsettings.json` connection string.
2. Run the Web project (F5 or `dotnet run` from `Web`).
3. Open `/` and try the Todo demo.

Dev endpoints:

- `/_swap/dev/events` — Event chains dashboard in Development
